OL,7,FThe first time David Jesudason walked
OL,8,Finto a pub, someone shouted out "taxi".
OL,9,FIt's a racist stereotype that people
OL,10,Ffrom South Asia drive cabs.
OL,12,FIt seemed unlikely the 15-year-old
OL,13,Fwould go on to work behind a bar at
OL,14,Funiversity and later become a director
OL,15,Fat the Beer Writers' Guild.
OL,17,FBut despite the racism he encountered,
OL,18,Fhe still remembers the "wonderful"
OL,19,Ftaste of his first pint, a Wadworth 6X
OL,20,Fbitter.
OL,3,CInside the history of desi pubs - the
OL,4,CBritish-Indian institution revitalising
OL,5,Cfailing boozers
